# Never Do

These are hard stops. No exceptions, no matter the justification.

## Infrastructure
- Never use FastAPI BackgroundTasks for ingestion, use ARQ workers
- Never install Qdrant, Redis, or Unstructured locally, use docker-compose
- Never use pip, always uv

## Data integrity
- Never query across company Qdrant collections
- Never store embeddings in memory, always persist to Qdrant
- Never skip namespacing by company_id on any Qdrant operation

## Retrieval
- Never do naive single-query dense-only retrieval
- Never skip query transformation before retrieval
- Never send raw user query directly to Qdrant without transformation

## LLM and streaming
- Never buffer the full LLM response, always stream via SSE
- Never fabricate citations or sources
- Never let the model answer outside of retrieved context

## Code quality
- Never use Pydantic v1 syntax anywhere
- Never read os.environ directly, always use core/config.py
- Never hardcode model names, chunk sizes, URLs, or top-k values
- Never use plain LangChain chains for the query pipeline, use LangGraph
- Never let raw library exceptions bubble up to routers
- Never use sync blocking calls inside async functions